Subject: African Americans--Civil rights
Name.subject: Bunche, Ralph J. (Ralph Johnson), $d 1904-1971
Name.repository: University of California, Los Angeles. $b Library Special Collections
Description.note: Digitization took place as part of the California Cultures Project.|~|Newspaper article, topped by a 13 x 24 cm. photograph with the caption: "Scenes like this from Birmingham, with police dogs used against negro demonstrators, have caused "very bad reactions" in Asia, Africa and Europe, says Ralph Bunche, Negro United Nations undersecretary, Bunche believes the situation climaxes a long struggle". Article also includes a photograph of Ralph Bunche with the caption : Ralph J. Bunche "Built-in impatience". Also includes a political cartoon by Justus, Minneapolis Star, with the caption: Extra! Extra! U.S. Race Riots All About the Race Riots in America
Title: Ralph Bunche On Integration : U.N. official says major breakthrough approaching : interview, the Courier-Journal, Louisville, Ky.
